50|$|Bradypodion caeruleogula, the Dhlinza <b>dwarf</b> <b>chameleon,</b> Eshowe <b>dwarf</b> <b>chameleon,</b> or uMlalazi <b>dwarf</b> <b>chameleon,</b> is {{endemic to}} KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. It {{is found in}} Dhlinza, Entumeni and Ongoye Forests.|$|R
50|$|Endemics to {{the area}} include a {{subspecies}} of crested guineafowl (Guttera edouardi symonsi), and a <b>dwarf</b> <b>chameleon</b> (Bradypodion sp.) which {{is related to the}} Natal Midlands <b>dwarf</b> <b>chameleon</b> and the black-headed <b>dwarf</b> <b>chameleon.</b>|$|R
